Both required outputs are written and validated.

**`transcript.json`**: 25 iterations, 38 hypotheses, 38 analyses, schema-validated. Covers main-effect screens for binary/continuous features, multivariable adjustment with race/insurance dummies, pairwise interactions among the top-effect features, three-way interactions for treatment × biomarker × biomarker, continuous biomarker effect modification, age × treatment / stage × treatment, quadratic age, lab-value screen, disparities in treatment receipt and outcome, and a final R² summary.

**`analysis_summary.txt`**: Narrative covering (1) main-effect predictors, (2) the null sociodemographic-disparity result for both race (feature_011) and insurance (feature_089) at every level tested, (3) the dominant clinical story — feature_042 looks like a targeted therapy whose +2.6–2.7-month PFS benefit is restricted to feature_111-positive, feature_015-negative, feature_040-negative, low-feature_101 patients (full interaction model R² = 0.889 vs 0.792 main-effects only), and (4) a hypothesis-by-hypothesis verdict.
